Blue baby. baby blue.

272
00:20:44.178 --> 00:20:46.379
Blue baby. baby blue.

273
00:20:46.446 --> 00:20:49.016
Blue baby. baby blue.

274
00:20:49.083 --> 00:20:51.119
Blue baby. baby blue.

275
00:20:51.185 --> 00:20:53.554
Blue baby. baby blue.

276
00:20:53.621 --> 00:20:56.023
Blue baby. baby blue...

277
00:20:56.090 --> 00:20:58.358
Blue baby. baby blue...

278
00:20:58.425 --> 00:21:01.195
Blue baby. baby blue...

279
00:21:01.328 --> 00:21:04.832
[woman vocalizing]

280
00:21:13.674 --> 00:21:16.144
-[knocks on door]
-Maureen?

281
00:21:16.210 --> 00:21:18.846
-You okay?
-I'll be out in a minute.

282
00:21:39.366 --> 00:21:42.837
[whispering voices]

283
00:21:48.375 --> 00:21:50.410
And she's back!

284
00:21:50.477 --> 00:21:52.847
So. did you see
any baby ghosts?

285
00:21:52.914 --> 00:21:54.649
No. not really.

286
00:21:55.616 --> 00:21:58.619
Well. actually.
I started feeling my arms

287
00:21:58.686 --> 00:22:00.755
getting a little
bit heavy but. like...

288
00:22:00.822 --> 00:22:03.090
I guess that's
because I held the position

289
00:22:03.157 --> 00:22:04.491
for a very long time. right?

290
00:22:04.559 --> 00:22:07.028
Yeah. right.
Or it's probably just Hunter

291
00:22:07.094 --> 00:22:10.565
playing a joke on you. Maureen.
I mean. he is such an idiot.

292
00:22:13.067 --> 00:22:14.769
[scoffs] Come on.

293
00:22:14.836 --> 00:22:17.071
you didn't really expect it
to work. right?

294
00:22:17.138 --> 00:22:18.639
It's just a game.

295
00:22:18.706 --> 00:22:20.908
Girls. if you're not gonna
take this seriously

296
00:22:20.975 --> 00:22:21.909
it's not gonna work!

297
00:22:21.976 --> 00:22:23.410
Okay. girl. I'm sorry!

298
00:22:23.410 --> 00:22:25.012
Okay.

299
00:22:26.247 --> 00:22:28.716
[sighs] Not all is lost.

300
00:22:30.284 --> 00:22:32.720
Didn't I say
there were two ways

301
00:22:32.787 --> 00:22:34.889
to play this challenge?

302
00:22:34.956 --> 00:22:36.456
That's true.

303
00:22:36.524 --> 00:22:39.260
I haven't explained
the second way. did I?

304
00:22:39.327 --> 00:22:41.229
Here we go again.

305
00:22:41.295 --> 00:22:43.865
So. the procedure
is very similar.

306
00:22:43.931 --> 00:22:46.601
Only this time.
you don't need to repeat.

307
00:22:46.667 --> 00:22:49.904
"baby blue. blue baby"
thirteen times.

308
00:22:49.971 --> 00:22:51.438
Instead.

309
00:22:51.471 --> 00:22:55.176
you're gonna
open the hot water.

310
00:22:55.243 --> 00:22:56.711
and let it run.

311
00:22:56.777 --> 00:23:00.314
until it fogs
the mirror completely.

312
00:23:00.447 --> 00:23:05.353
and you are gonna
write "Baby blue" on it.

313
00:23:05.452 --> 00:23:08.589
And Stace. sugar.
I think it is your turn.

314
00:23:11.659 --> 00:23:15.863
Okay. I think I have
a good story to tell.

315
00:23:19.466 --> 00:23:22.469
Ooh. spooky...

316
00:23:25.306 --> 00:23:26.807
Hm.

317
00:23:34.115 --> 00:23:37.018
Okay. first. hot water.

318
00:23:38.286 --> 00:23:40.922
Step two. story.

319
00:23:40.988 --> 00:23:43.524
Okay. So. the story
my friend told me.

320
00:23:43.591 --> 00:23:45.826
goes something like this...

321
00:23:47.728 --> 00:23:50.497
[woman humming]

322
00:24:02.109 --> 00:24:04.879
[humming continues]

323
00:24:10.785 --> 00:24:14.522
[rock music playing
over headphones]

324
00:24:16.824 --> 00:24:18.559
[dog barking in distance]

325
00:24:38.546 --> 00:24:40.815
Hey. look who's here.

326
00:24:40.881 --> 00:24:41.916
It's Ana.

327
00:24:44.552 --> 00:24:47.221
Uh. where's Mom?

328
00:24:47.288 --> 00:24:49.724
I don't know.
She hasn't been here all day.

329
00:24:49.790 --> 00:24:51.359
But I mean.
her car is still here.

330
00:24:51.425 --> 00:24:52.994
her purse is over there...

331
00:24:53.060 --> 00:24:55.262
It's fine. though.
I'm taking care of Yaya.

332
00:24:55.329 --> 00:24:57.131
[Ana]
Looks fun.

333
00:24:57.198 --> 00:24:58.899
[phone rings]

334
00:24:58.966 --> 00:25:01.769
-Okay.
-Hello? <i>Hola</i> .

335
00:25:01.836 --> 00:25:03.204
Yeah. Ana just got here.

336
00:25:03.270 --> 00:25:05.773
She's home from school
for the long weekend.

337
00:25:30.331 --> 00:25:31.699
[dripping]

338
00:25:39.106 --> 00:25:40.741
Okay. um...

339
00:25:44.612 --> 00:25:46.080
I'm gonna...

340
00:25:52.253 --> 00:25:53.721
Aww. look at you two.

341
00:25:53.788 --> 00:25:54.855
Is she getting worse?

342
00:25:54.922 --> 00:25:57.091
[whispered voices]
<i>Run.</i>

343
00:25:57.158 --> 00:25:59.060
Don't grab Yaya's hand
like that.

344
00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:01.095
That hurts her.

345
00:26:01.162 --> 00:26:02.096
Oh. my goodness.

346
00:26:02.163 --> 00:26:04.198
I don't what's gotten into her.

347
00:26:06.133 --> 00:26:07.435
Oh. god.

348
00:26:07.501 --> 00:26:09.203
Mari. oh. my god.

349
00:26:10.704 --> 00:26:12.273
Come here.

350
00:26:12.339 --> 00:26:13.808
What is that?

351
00:26:19.413 --> 00:26:20.781
No.

352
00:26:21.649 --> 00:26:23.818
Okay. Oh.

353
00:26:23.884 --> 00:26:26.353
Get over yourself
and come help me. please.

354
00:26:26.420 --> 00:26:27.955
Just gimme a sec.

355
00:26:28.956 --> 00:26:30.091
Okay.

356
00:26:32.326 --> 00:26:33.528
How's Chicago?

357
00:26:33.661 --> 00:26:35.162
Cold.

358
00:26:35.229 --> 00:26:37.264
[Mari] I've been dying
to go visit you.

359
00:26:37.331 --> 00:26:39.733
Then why haven't you?
I have an extra bed.

360
00:26:39.800 --> 00:26:42.470
I can't just leave here.

361
00:26:42.537 --> 00:26:45.673
Okay. there we go.

362
00:26:45.706 --> 00:26:48.109
Someone needs to help
take care of Yaya.

363
00:26:52.313 --> 00:26:54.215
[Velcro ripping]

364
00:26:56.383 --> 00:26:58.052
Okay.

365
00:27:03.525 --> 00:27:05.059
[Ana gags]

366
00:27:08.162 --> 00:27:10.498
[Yaya moaning]

367
00:27:10.565 --> 00:27:12.199
It's Mom's bracelet.

368
00:27:13.234 --> 00:27:14.935
Oh. my-- Oh. my--

369
00:27:17.471 --> 00:27:19.773
Ana. Ana. please.

370
00:27:20.808 --> 00:27:23.144
None of this is normal. right?

371
00:27:23.210 --> 00:27:24.345
No. Mari.

372
00:27:24.411 --> 00:27:26.947
Why's Mommy's bracelet
in Yaya's diaper?

373
00:27:27.014 --> 00:27:29.817
I don't know. [chuckling]
For safekeeping?

374
00:27:30.751 --> 00:27:32.186
Safekeeping.

375
00:27:40.094 --> 00:27:42.564
Every time I come home.
I'm just...

376
00:27:43.397 --> 00:27:45.933
terrified that I'm
gonna end up stuck here.

377
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:48.435
covered in shit and puke.

378
00:27:48.503 --> 00:27:49.470
-just like--
-Mom?

379
00:27:49.538 --> 00:27:50.905
God. no. You.

380
00:27:54.775 --> 00:27:56.377
-Wait--
-It's fine.

381
00:27:56.443 --> 00:27:58.279
I'll finish up alone. okay?

382
00:27:59.346 --> 00:28:01.782
Yeah. Sure.

383
00:28:11.792 --> 00:28:13.595
Remember how mad
Mom would get

384
00:28:13.662 --> 00:28:15.362
if she caught us
in Yaya's room?

385
00:28:16.230 --> 00:28:18.499
I wonder how far back these go.

386
00:28:18.567 --> 00:28:22.671
[Mari] Yeah. So many <i>tios</i>
and <i>tias</i> we've never met.

387
00:28:22.770 --> 00:28:24.506
Feels like they're all
in this room.

388
00:28:24.573 --> 00:28:26.106
staring at us.

389
00:28:32.079 --> 00:28:34.848
Do you... think Mom's okay?

390
00:28:35.783 --> 00:28:37.519
Yeah. of course.

391
00:28:37.586 --> 00:28:40.788
She'll turn up soon. [chuckles]

392
00:28:45.993 --> 00:28:47.895
I-I'm really glad you're here.

393
00:28:49.797 --> 00:28:51.031
Yeah.

394
00:28:53.668 --> 00:28:55.503
I'll make some dinner. okay?

395
00:29:22.429 --> 00:29:23.497
Yaya?

396
00:29:36.910 --> 00:29:40.381
[voices whisper]

397
00:29:40.447 --> 00:29:42.584
[Ana]
How old are you?

398
00:29:43.217 --> 00:29:46.387
[Hispanic music playing
on radio]

399
00:29:57.298 --> 00:29:58.232
Mari.

400
00:29:58.299 --> 00:30:00.200
[Mari]
Dinner's almost ready!

401
00:30:06.373 --> 00:30:09.443
[grunting]

402
00:30:12.913 --> 00:30:17.985
[voices whispering]
Run. my daughter. Run.

403
00:30:24.659 --> 00:30:27.328
Run. run. run. Run!

404
00:30:27.394 --> 00:30:28.862
[growls]

405
00:30:28.929 --> 00:30:32.299
[vomiting]

406
00:30:39.006 --> 00:30:40.542
Ana. why's Yaya on the floor?

407
00:30:40.608 --> 00:30:43.578
I'm not like you. okay?
I can't do this family shit.

408
00:30:43.645 --> 00:30:47.615
or the shit that she says to me
or the literal shit. shit!

409
00:30:47.682 --> 00:30:49.249
You think I want this life?

410
00:30:49.316 --> 00:30:51.018
I do this
because somebody has to!

411
00:30:51.085 --> 00:30:52.986
Somebody has to.
I'm trying to help you!

412
00:30:53.053 --> 00:30:54.288
I'm not asking you to!

413
00:30:54.355 --> 00:30:55.956
-Family cares!
-Oh. my god.

414
00:30:56.023 --> 00:30:58.025
[door opens. closes]

415
00:30:58.092 --> 00:31:00.461
[Yaya groaning]

416
00:31:06.701 --> 00:31:09.069
[groaning]

417
00:31:11.639 --> 00:31:12.940
I can't do this anymore.

418
00:31:12.973 --> 00:31:14.942
[sighs]

419
00:31:19.246 --> 00:31:21.281
[whispers]
She won't like it.

420
00:31:25.285 --> 00:31:26.186
Mom?

421
00:31:26.253 --> 00:31:29.056
Yaya. listen. Yaya.

422
00:31:29.858 --> 00:31:32.059
She's a monster.

423
00:31:33.460 --> 00:31:34.529
No.

424
00:31:36.698 --> 00:31:40.267
[struggling]

425
00:31:40.334 --> 00:31:42.704
Ow! Ow!

426
00:31:42.771 --> 00:31:44.037
Stop!

427
00:31:44.104 --> 00:31:46.440
Stop. Yaya! Stop!

428
00:31:46.508 --> 00:31:47.675
Stop!

429
00:31:47.742 --> 00:31:50.978
-[growls]
-[screams]

430
00:31:52.112 --> 00:31:54.314
[Mira screams]

431
00:31:55.983 --> 00:31:59.521
[music muffled
through headphones]

432
00:32:03.725 --> 00:32:05.292
[electrical zapping]

433
00:32:24.011 --> 00:32:26.514
[voices whispering]

434
00:32:26.581 --> 00:32:28.683
[squelching]

435
00:32:40.862 --> 00:32:42.597
-[voices distorted] <i>Ana.</i>
-[gasps]

436
00:32:44.465 --> 00:32:46.935
[voices whispering]
<i>Ana. We're all in here.</i>

437
00:32:47.034 --> 00:32:48.302
<i>We're all in here.</i>

438
00:33:01.281 --> 00:33:03.383
[voices whisper]
<i>You have to go.</i>

439
00:33:04.552 --> 00:33:06.754
<i>Don't get stuck here like us.</i>

440
00:33:08.455 --> 00:33:09.557
Mom?

441
00:33:12.359 --> 00:33:14.428
Wait. What happens
to you if I leave?

442
00:33:14.495 --> 00:33:17.231
[voices] <i>You can survive</i>
<i>and you'll be free.</i>

443
00:33:17.297 --> 00:33:18.666
I don't understand.

444
00:33:18.733 --> 00:33:21.301
[voices]
<i>Live your life.</i>

445
00:33:21.368 --> 00:33:23.370
<i>And never look back!</i>

446
00:33:23.437 --> 00:33:26.106
<i>Run! Go away. leave us!</i>

447
00:33:31.144 --> 00:33:32.580
<i>Ana.</i>

448
00:33:38.920 --> 00:33:40.153
Mari?

449
00:33:40.220 --> 00:33:41.556
[voices]
<i>Ana.</i>

450
00:33:43.658 --> 00:33:46.493
<i>I don't know where I am.</i>
<i>I'm scared.</i>

451
00:33:47.929 --> 00:33:50.632
<i>There are so many people. Ana.</i>

452
00:33:50.698 --> 00:33:52.299
<i>Ana. please.</i>

453
00:33:56.871 --> 00:33:58.506
<i>I need you.</i>

454
00:34:18.826 --> 00:34:21.529
[woman humming]

455
00:34:44.251 --> 00:34:46.386
[humming continues]

456
00:34:49.524 --> 00:34:51.659
-[water running]
-[Stacey sighs]

457
00:34:57.699 --> 00:34:59.232
Baby...

458
00:35:00.768 --> 00:35:01.803
blue.

459
00:35:07.008 --> 00:35:08.342
Perfect.

460
00:35:17.852 --> 00:35:20.487
[tense tone]

461
00:35:31.198 --> 00:35:33.768
[baby crying]

462
00:35:35.069 --> 00:35:37.639
[Stacey screams]

463
00:35:41.743 --> 00:35:42.977
[gasps]

464
00:35:43.044 --> 00:35:44.045
What happened?

465
00:35:44.112 --> 00:35:45.212
Stacey?

466
00:35:45.245 --> 00:35:46.814
I saw the baby.

467
00:35:46.881 --> 00:35:49.216
[breathing heavily]

468
00:35:55.322 --> 00:35:57.725
[doorbell buzzes]

469
00:35:57.792 --> 00:35:59.226
It's Hunter.

470
00:36:04.132 --> 00:36:06.000
[exhales heavily]

471
00:36:06.067 --> 00:36:07.669
Stacey.

472
00:36:08.569 --> 00:36:10.705
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

473
00:36:14.241 --> 00:36:15.843
Breath. yes.

474
00:36:20.882 --> 00:36:22.249
Yes.

475
00:36:25.520 --> 00:36:27.689
Hey. girls. how's it going?

476
00:36:28.790 --> 00:36:30.792
Stace. Laura.

477
00:36:31.826 --> 00:36:33.094
That's rude.

478
00:36:33.161 --> 00:36:34.996
That is what I was trying
to tell you.

479
00:36:35.063 --> 00:36:36.496
Stacey saw the baby.

480
00:36:36.564 --> 00:36:38.498
-Seriously?
-Yes.

481
00:36:39.433 --> 00:36:42.335
Hey. Stace. you saw the baby?

482
00:36:43.137 --> 00:36:44.371
I don't know...

483
00:36:45.606 --> 00:36:49.110
But you let go of the baby
in time. right?

484
00:36:49.177 --> 00:36:50.778
-Right?
-Yeah. I don't know.

485
00:36:50.845 --> 00:36:52.013
I don't know!

486
00:36:52.080 --> 00:36:55.282
[baby crying on monitor]

487
00:36:58.418 --> 00:37:00.521
I gotta check on Bobby.
I'll be right back.

488
00:37:00.588 --> 00:37:02.890
[baby continues crying
on monitor]

489
00:37:05.960 --> 00:37:08.295
I told you. I said
we shouldn't include Laura.

490
00:37:08.361 --> 00:37:10.464
Why would you think
it's a good idea.

491
00:37:10.531 --> 00:37:12.299
to invite someone who
just lost a baby a year ago.

492
00:37:12.365 --> 00:37:14.902
to play a game where we summon
the spirit of a dead child.

493
00:37:14.969 --> 00:37:16.204
it's ridiculous.

494
00:37:16.303 --> 00:37:17.772
[Maureen]
That was two years ago.

495
00:37:17.839 --> 00:37:19.540
[Hunter] Two years.
three years. who gives a shit!

496
00:37:19.607 --> 00:37:21.374
[Maureen] Oh. my god.
you're so exaggerated.

497
00:37:21.441 --> 00:37:22.577
[Hunter]
Shut up. it's too late.

498
00:37:22.643 --> 00:37:24.311
You shouldn't have been here!

499
00:37:35.422 --> 00:37:38.893
[crackling on monitor]

500
00:37:52.907 --> 00:37:55.877
[crackling on monitor
continues]

501
00:38:04.919 --> 00:38:08.355
[footsteps approach]

502
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:13.961
You okay?

503
00:38:14.028 --> 00:38:16.831
Yeah. Everything is fine.

504
00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:22.637
Okay. I'm sorry
to be so pushy.

505
00:38:22.703 --> 00:38:24.539
but if we want
to get rid of the spirit

506
00:38:24.605 --> 00:38:26.240
we need to do
the ritual right now.

507
00:38:26.373 --> 00:38:28.976
Oh. my god. we don't even know
if there's a spirit in here.

508
00:38:29.043 --> 00:38:30.377
We don't know what we know.

509
00:38:30.377 --> 00:38:31.946
She doesn't even know
what she saw!

510
00:38:32.013 --> 00:38:34.582
Okay. calm your shit.
What. are you scared right now?

511
00:38:34.649 --> 00:38:36.717
I am just saying that

512
00:38:36.784 --> 00:38:39.787
we could do the ritual anyway.
Just in case.

513
00:38:41.122 --> 00:38:42.590
What should we do?

514
00:38:44.525 --> 00:38:46.260
[sighs]
There's only one thing to do

515
00:38:46.393 --> 00:38:47.762
once the rules are broken.

516
00:38:49.230 --> 00:38:50.832
We need to face the ghost.

517
00:38:52.399 --> 00:38:55.402
One must enter the room.
face the mirror.

518
00:38:55.435 --> 00:38:57.104
holding baby blue in his arms.

519
00:38:58.405 --> 00:39:00.041
And wait for the mother
to appear.

520
00:39:01.108 --> 00:39:02.743
No matter what she does.

521
00:39:02.810 --> 00:39:05.746
one must remain silent
and still.

522
00:39:08.316 --> 00:39:09.784
And that way you can show her

523
00:39:09.851 --> 00:39:12.086
that you are fit
to take care of the baby.

524
00:39:13.554 --> 00:39:15.690
I'm not going in there again.

525
00:39:15.756 --> 00:39:17.525
[Laura]
No.

526
00:39:17.592 --> 00:39:19.160
you should do it.

527
00:39:19.227 --> 00:39:21.128
You got us into this mess.

528
00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:28.069
Babe. please.

529
00:39:28.135 --> 00:39:30.538
You are the only one
that played the game.

530
00:39:30.605 --> 00:39:33.507
[sighs] Fine. I'll do it.

531
00:39:35.610 --> 00:39:37.011
I'll do it.

532
00:39:49.156 --> 00:39:51.092
[door creaks]

533
00:39:57.164 --> 00:39:58.933
[exhales]

534
00:40:06.307 --> 00:40:07.842
[exhales]

535
00:40:09.277 --> 00:40:11.779
[water running]

536
00:40:20.655 --> 00:40:22.455
I don't know
if this is gonna work.

537
00:40:22.523 --> 00:40:23.858
Here I go.

538
00:40:36.370 --> 00:40:38.973
[tense tone]

539
00:40:40.608 --> 00:40:43.110
[toy creaks]

540
00:40:43.177 --> 00:40:45.445
[toy playing
gentle kalimba music]

541
00:40:49.449 --> 00:40:52.553
[water running]

542
00:41:19.981 --> 00:41:24.118
[door buzzing]

543
00:41:28.022 --> 00:41:30.291
-[water stops]
-[door buzzing]

544
00:41:30.358 --> 00:41:32.560
Yeah. yeah. I hear you.

545
00:41:48.109 --> 00:41:50.578
Yeah? Who is it?

546
00:41:52.146 --> 00:41:53.848
[man over speaker]
<i>Locksmith.</i>

547
00:41:55.249 --> 00:41:57.752
[buzzes]

548
00:41:59.253 --> 00:42:00.321
[door opens. closes]

549
00:42:00.388 --> 00:42:03.691
[footsteps up stairs]

550
00:42:06.594 --> 00:42:08.095
[knock on door]

551
00:42:16.170 --> 00:42:18.172
[unlocks door]

552
00:42:18.239 --> 00:42:19.673
It's about damn time.

553
00:42:19.740 --> 00:42:21.909
I told the landlord
about this weeks ago.

554
00:42:31.185 --> 00:42:32.820
Is it this lock?

555
00:42:33.788 --> 00:42:35.089
The back door.

556
00:42:35.156 --> 00:42:37.158
Come on. I have
to get ready for work.

557
00:42:42.229 --> 00:42:43.330
[door closes]

558
00:42:44.331 --> 00:42:49.136
Oh. I really like the way
you have the place decorated.

559
00:42:51.540 --> 00:42:54.642
The door's in the kitchen.
at the end of the hall.

560
00:43:16.330 --> 00:43:18.933
[floorboards creak]

561
00:43:30.711 --> 00:43:32.680
[floorboards creak]

562
00:44:12.286 --> 00:44:14.088
-[floorboards creak]
-Jesus!

563
00:44:15.022 --> 00:44:16.757
The machine was beeping.

564
00:44:16.824 --> 00:44:18.993
It seems like you're in a rush.

565
00:44:37.945 --> 00:44:41.550
Were you looking for something
in my living room?

566
00:44:41.616 --> 00:44:43.984
[locksmith] Yeah. I thought
I brought my hammer in.

567
00:44:44.051 --> 00:44:46.287
but I guess I must have
left it out in the truck.

568
00:44:46.353 --> 00:44:48.856
I'll go out
and get it in a second.

569
00:44:54.663 --> 00:44:56.163
[scoffs]

570
00:45:26.493 --> 00:45:27.795
[gasps]

571
00:45:45.179 --> 00:45:47.381
This shouldn't take very long.

572
00:45:48.215 --> 00:45:49.817
I can lock up when I'm done

573
00:45:49.883 --> 00:45:51.952
so you don't have
to wait around.

574
00:46:00.562 --> 00:46:03.230
You need to leave. right now.

575
00:46:06.166 --> 00:46:07.001
What?

576
00:46:07.067 --> 00:46:09.537
Get out of my house!

577
00:46:20.682 --> 00:46:22.216
You don't want me
to fix your lock?

578
00:46:22.283 --> 00:46:23.752
No. I can find someone else

579
00:46:23.851 --> 00:46:25.754
who can keep his hands
off my things.

580
00:46:25.853 --> 00:46:28.022
Hey. I'm sorry
your coffee was ready.

581
00:46:28.088 --> 00:46:30.357
I was just trying
to be helpful.

582
00:46:38.533 --> 00:46:40.934
Are you kidding me?

583
00:46:43.270 --> 00:46:45.272
Get out!

584
00:46:45.339 --> 00:46:46.874
Go!

585
00:46:51.646 --> 00:46:55.517
[door closes. locks]

586
00:47:25.379 --> 00:47:28.248
[tense tone]

587
00:47:47.434 --> 00:47:50.505
[mirror squeaking]

588
00:48:04.351 --> 00:48:06.387
[squeaking]

589
00:48:06.453 --> 00:48:10.023
[creaking]

590
00:49:07.448 --> 00:49:08.716
Okay.

591
00:49:10.652 --> 00:49:12.119
[wind whooshes]

592
00:49:16.156 --> 00:49:20.562
[voices whispering]

593
00:49:20.628 --> 00:49:25.165
Give me back my baby!

594
00:49:26.033 --> 00:49:28.670
[crackling]

595
00:49:30.705 --> 00:49:32.039
Oh!

596
00:49:32.874 --> 00:49:33.842
[whimpering]

597
00:49:33.908 --> 00:49:35.577
Oh. my god.

598
00:49:35.643 --> 00:49:37.478
What happened?

599
00:49:37.545 --> 00:49:39.179
What happened?

600
00:49:39.246 --> 00:49:40.715
[Hunter]
She attacked me.

601
00:49:40.782 --> 00:49:43.283
We need to take Hunter
to the hospital right now!

602
00:49:43.751 --> 00:49:47.622
I'm not leaving the baby alone
in this house!

603
00:49:47.689 --> 00:49:49.624
She's in the house.

604
00:49:49.691 --> 00:49:51.158
She's in the hou...

605
00:49:52.159 --> 00:49:53.628
I'll do it.

606
00:49:54.228 --> 00:49:56.163
Take Hunter to the hospital.

607
00:49:57.966 --> 00:49:59.801
Babe. help me. Help me!

608
00:49:59.868 --> 00:50:01.401
Yes. come...

609
00:50:02.169 --> 00:50:04.506
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
-[Hunter whimpering]

610
00:50:12.479 --> 00:50:13.548
Laura...

611
00:50:17.184 --> 00:50:19.019
Let's end this.

612
00:51:03.363 --> 00:51:05.232
[tense tone]

613
00:51:28.056 --> 00:51:30.725
[waves rushing]

614
00:51:34.929 --> 00:51:37.532
-[phone ringing]
-[Rachel] Hello?

615
00:51:37.599 --> 00:51:40.167
[man] <i>Hi. I'm calling from</i>
<i>the Orchard Police Department.</i>

616
00:51:40.200 --> 00:51:43.170
<i>Can I confirm that I'm</i>
<i>speaking with Rachel Dodson?</i>

617
00:51:43.170 --> 00:51:44.739
[Rachel]
Uh. yeah. that's me.

618
00:51:44.806 --> 00:51:46.975
[man] <i>I hate to be doing this</i>
<i>over the phone.</i>

619
00:51:47.041 --> 00:51:48.342
<i>but I regret to inform you</i>

620
00:51:48.408 --> 00:51:50.210
<i>that your father's</i>
<i>passed away.</i>

621
00:51:50.277 --> 00:51:51.378
[Rachel]
What?

622
00:51:51.445 --> 00:51:52.614
[man]
<i>I'm very sorry.</i>

623
00:51:52.680 --> 00:51:54.515
<i>Do you have any family in town</i>

624
00:51:54.582 --> 00:51:56.551
<i>that can take care</i>
<i>of things here?</i>

625
00:51:56.618 --> 00:51:57.986
[Rachel]
No.

626
00:51:58.052 --> 00:51:59.687
No. it's just me.

627
00:53:06.286 --> 00:53:07.822
[Rachel's father]
<i>So. you like coming</i>

628
00:53:07.889 --> 00:53:09.891
<i>to Grandma and Grandpa's</i>
<i>for summer. hey?</i>

629
00:53:09.957 --> 00:53:11.291
-[Rachel] <i>Yeah.</i>
-[father] <i>Yeah?</i>

630
00:53:11.358 --> 00:53:12.760
<i>Summer's almost over. though.</i>

631
00:53:12.827 --> 00:53:14.494
[Rachel] <i>Yeah.</i>
<i>I want it to be longer.</i>

632
00:53:14.562 --> 00:53:16.296
[Rachel's father]
<i>You want it to be longer?</i>

633
00:53:16.363 --> 00:53:19.266
<i>Well. you're looking forward</i>
<i>to school there. aren't ya?</i>

634
00:53:19.266 --> 00:53:21.368
<i>-Yeah.</i>
-[Rachel's father] <i>Yeah?</i>

635
00:53:21.435 --> 00:53:24.337
<i>It doesn't sound like you are.</i>
[laughs]

636
00:53:24.404 --> 00:53:25.773
<i>Yeah. I know.</i>

637
00:53:25.840 --> 00:53:28.009
[Rachel's father]
<i>Yeah. A little bit?</i>

638
00:53:28.076 --> 00:53:31.045
<i>It'll be nice to see</i>
<i>your friends again.</i>

639
00:53:31.112 --> 00:53:32.580
<i>Yeah. I miss them.</i>

640
00:53:32.647 --> 00:53:34.414
<i>but I really like</i>
<i>coming here. though.</i>

641
00:53:34.481 --> 00:53:36.383
[Rachel's father]
<i>Yeah.</i>

642
00:53:43.558 --> 00:53:45.993
[breathing heavily]

643
00:53:48.029 --> 00:53:49.463
<i>Oh. god.</i>

644
00:53:50.464 --> 00:53:53.801
<i>I miss you so much.</i>

645
00:53:56.104 --> 00:53:57.337
<i>Now.</i>

646
00:53:58.506 --> 00:54:01.576
<i>there's no one</i>
<i>left in the house.</i>

647
00:54:03.911 --> 00:54:07.949
[sighs] <i>I don't even</i>
<i>know what I'm doing.</i>

648
00:54:10.151 --> 00:54:12.653
<i>I just. I just need...</i>

649
00:54:13.855 --> 00:54:15.322
<i>someone.</i>

650
00:54:19.193 --> 00:54:21.996
[breathing heavily]

651
00:54:23.865 --> 00:54:26.167
[gulping]

652
00:54:26.234 --> 00:54:28.803
[breathing heavily]

653
00:54:32.740 --> 00:54:35.777
<i>There's no one</i>
<i>left in the house!</i>

654
00:54:35.843 --> 00:54:38.613
[sobbing]

655
00:54:45.787 --> 00:54:48.421
[gasps. whimpers]

656
00:54:53.194 --> 00:54:55.362
<i>There's no one in the house.</i>

657
00:54:56.931 --> 00:54:58.566
<i>There's no one.</i>

658
00:55:01.602 --> 00:55:03.704
<i>-</i> [banging]
-[shouting]

659
00:55:03.771 --> 00:55:05.606
[static]

660
00:55:10.244 --> 00:55:11.478
[clicks TV off]

661
00:55:11.546 --> 00:55:14.649
[floorboards creak]

662
00:55:48.983 --> 00:55:52.485
[menacing tone]

663
00:56:20.081 --> 00:56:22.449
[tone escalates]

664
00:56:35.462 --> 00:56:38.866
[pulsating tone]

665
00:56:44.005 --> 00:56:46.774
[child] <i>Help!</i>
<i>Somebody. please. help me!</i>

666
00:56:46.841 --> 00:56:49.176
<i>Grandma. Grandpa.</i>
<i>what are you doing up there?</i>

667
00:56:49.243 --> 00:56:51.245
<i>Please. come down!</i>

668
00:56:51.312 --> 00:56:52.713
<i>Help! Somebody help!</i>

669
00:56:52.780 --> 00:56:55.516
<i>Please. come down!</i>
<i>You're scaring me!</i>

670
00:56:55.583 --> 00:56:58.786
<i>Grandma! Grandpa! No!</i>

671
00:56:58.853 --> 00:57:00.688
[thuds]

672
00:57:13.167 --> 00:57:15.670
[man over radio]
<i>Garrick. what's your 20?</i>

673
00:57:20.141 --> 00:57:22.343
Yeah. just a quick pit stop
at home.

674
00:57:22.410 --> 00:57:25.846
[man] <i>Copy that. We got</i>
<i>a 10-54 over on State Street.</i>

675
00:57:35.389 --> 00:57:36.924
Yeah. I'm on my way.

676
00:57:38.225 --> 00:57:39.593
[radio clunks]

677
00:57:41.696 --> 00:57:43.998
-[keys jingle]
-[engine starts]

678
00:57:54.008 --> 00:57:55.943
Hey. You know Rachel
that called this in?

679
00:57:56.010 --> 00:57:58.612
She's staying at that place
from a couple weeks ago.

680
00:57:58.679 --> 00:58:00.448
-The Dodson house?
-Yeah.

681
00:58:00.548 --> 00:58:03.884
[radio chatter]

682
00:58:18.466 --> 00:58:20.401
[answering machine]
<i>First new message.</i> [beeps]

683
00:58:20.468 --> 00:58:23.204
[on machine] <i>Hi Rachel.</i>
<i>This is Officer Garrick.</i>

684
00:58:23.270 --> 00:58:25.606
<i>Apologies I missed you</i>
<i>at the scene today.</i>

685
00:58:25.673 --> 00:58:27.274
<i>but I'd like you</i>
<i>to give me a call</i>

686
00:58:27.341 --> 00:58:28.876
<i>when you have a moment.</i>

687
00:58:28.943 --> 00:58:30.878
<i>There's some details.</i>
<i>irregularities I'd like</i>

688
00:58:30.945 --> 00:58:32.646
<i>to discuss</i>
<i>about your father's case.</i>

689
00:58:32.713 --> 00:58:36.317
<i>You can reach me</i>
<i>at (310) 551-0157.</i>

690
00:58:36.384 --> 00:58:37.752
[call disconnects]

691
00:58:46.494 --> 00:58:49.597
[birds chirping]

692
00:58:53.601 --> 00:58:55.069
[knock at door]

693
00:59:01.042 --> 00:59:01.909
Hey.

694
00:59:01.976 --> 00:59:03.644
-[Rachel] Hi.
-Hi.

695
00:59:03.711 --> 00:59:06.313
-Thanks for coming over.
-No trouble.

696
00:59:06.380 --> 00:59:10.818
It's a crazy day. so
whatever I can do to help.

697
00:59:12.319 --> 00:59:14.955
I was wondering if we
could talk about my father.

698
00:59:15.022 --> 00:59:18.292
[chuckles]
what you mentioned before.

699
00:59:18.359 --> 00:59:19.760
Right. Well. uh...

700
00:59:21.295 --> 00:59:25.366
He was found way out
in that old cellar.

701
00:59:25.433 --> 00:59:26.634
at the end of the driveway.

702
00:59:26.667 --> 00:59:28.135
What?

703
00:59:28.702 --> 00:59:30.471
Was this not discussed
with you?

704
00:59:30.539 --> 00:59:33.841
No. No. no one told me that.

705
00:59:33.908 --> 00:59:35.776
Well. he was found
on the stairs

706
00:59:35.843 --> 00:59:39.847
with what was diagnosed
as cardiac arrest. yes.

707
00:59:39.914 --> 00:59:41.649
He was also found
with his hands

708
00:59:41.682 --> 00:59:44.385
against the doors
with significant wounds

709
00:59:44.452 --> 00:59:45.753
in his fingers.

710
00:59:47.021 --> 00:59:48.689
As if he was trying to get out.

711
00:59:52.893 --> 00:59:55.763
I'm sorry. I know this is
a lot to process right now.

712
01:00:00.034 --> 01:00:02.069
He struggled with alcohol.

713
01:00:02.970 --> 01:00:04.972
for as long as I can remember.

714
01:00:07.875 --> 01:00:10.044
[sighs] And then.
when my mom passed away.

715
01:00:10.111 --> 01:00:12.947
he would've been here
all alone. so...

716
01:00:16.317 --> 01:00:19.220
So. you were the one
who found him?

717
01:00:19.286 --> 01:00:20.955
I did. yes.

718
01:00:21.722 --> 01:00:25.926
I took the call and I was
the first one to arrive here.

719
01:00:25.993 --> 01:00:28.362
Look. apologies.
I should get going.

720
01:00:28.429 --> 01:00:31.398
Anytime. you call me
if you need anything.

721
01:00:32.466 --> 01:00:33.767
Mm-hmm.

722
01:00:36.670 --> 01:00:39.373
[car door opens. closes]

723
01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:40.841
[car starts]

724
01:01:07.902 --> 01:01:12.273
[clock ticking]

725
01:01:16.744 --> 01:01:19.813
[rustling. scratching]

726
01:01:43.470 --> 01:01:45.507
[screams]

727
01:01:45.574 --> 01:01:47.174
[gasps]

728
01:01:48.643 --> 01:01:50.778
[panting]

729
01:01:54.516 --> 01:01:58.452
[baby whining]

730
01:01:58.520 --> 01:02:01.288
[baby crying]

731
01:02:07.529 --> 01:02:11.465
[crying continues]

732
01:02:15.302 --> 01:02:18.339
[crying continues]

733
01:02:25.680 --> 01:02:27.314
-[boards rattling]
-[gasps]

734
01:02:32.186 --> 01:02:34.589
-Hey. hey! Can you help me?
-What is it?

735
01:02:34.656 --> 01:02:37.258
I just. I need to show you
something in the yard.

736
01:02:37.324 --> 01:02:39.827
I think s-someone is there.
maybe.

737
01:02:41.061 --> 01:02:42.997
There's these hand prints
on the window

738
01:02:43.063 --> 01:02:44.431
and it's kind of fucked up.

739
01:02:44.498 --> 01:02:46.000
so could you just come
with me. please?

740
01:02:46.066 --> 01:02:48.502
I've tried to get
a hold of Garrick.

741
01:02:48.570 --> 01:02:50.938
He's going through a
family emergency right now.

742
01:02:51.005 --> 01:02:52.439
Is he all right?

743
01:02:52.507 --> 01:02:53.841
I guess you haven't heard?

744
01:02:53.841 --> 01:02:55.510
His kid went missing
last night.

745
01:02:55.577 --> 01:02:56.844
What?

746
01:02:56.877 --> 01:02:58.946
The AMBER alert
just got sent out.

747
01:02:59.847 --> 01:03:01.583
Is it just up here?

748
01:03:01.650 --> 01:03:04.586
Yeah. It's just there.
on the edge of the woods.

749
01:03:04.653 --> 01:03:07.054
[footsteps recede]

750
01:03:10.725 --> 01:03:12.993
Ma'am. get inside. please!

751
01:03:13.060 --> 01:03:15.229
-What is it?
-Get inside now!

752
01:03:50.030 --> 01:03:52.499
[officer vomiting]

753
01:03:54.803 --> 01:03:56.470
[Rachel]
Jesus. Are you okay?

754
01:03:56.538 --> 01:03:57.639
[indistinct whispers]

755
01:03:57.706 --> 01:03:58.707
Hey. is everything all right?

756
01:03:58.773 --> 01:04:01.241
[indistinct whispers]

757
01:04:01.308 --> 01:04:04.311
[officer distorted voice]
Why did you leave me. Rachel?

758
01:04:05.212 --> 01:04:06.614
What?

759
01:04:06.681 --> 01:04:10.084
[officer distorted] Why did
you leave me here with her?

760
01:04:16.591 --> 01:04:18.125
What?

761
01:04:18.192 --> 01:04:19.460
-[squelches]
-[gasps]

762
01:04:19.527 --> 01:04:22.530
[gurgling]

763
01:04:22.597 --> 01:04:25.299
[gasping scream] No!

764
01:04:25.366 --> 01:04:26.934
[gurgling]

765
01:04:26.967 --> 01:04:28.636
[body thuds]

766
01:04:28.703 --> 01:04:31.972
[sobbing]

767
01:04:32.039 --> 01:04:35.577
[baby crying in distance]

768
01:04:35.643 --> 01:04:38.713
[Rachel sobbing]

769
01:04:38.780 --> 01:04:42.082
[panting]

770
01:04:42.149 --> 01:04:44.753
[baby crying]

771
01:04:44.819 --> 01:04:48.656
[breathing shakily]

772
01:04:48.723 --> 01:04:51.425
[baby continues crying]

773
01:05:00.968 --> 01:05:04.606
[panting]

774
01:05:06.708 --> 01:05:09.143
[baby continues crying]

775
01:05:15.115 --> 01:05:17.017
[dark pulsating tone]

776
01:05:21.422 --> 01:05:22.456
Mathews?

777
01:05:23.658 --> 01:05:25.192
Mathews?!

778
01:05:35.904 --> 01:05:39.306
[Rachel gasps. screams]

779
01:05:40.474 --> 01:05:43.377
Who the fuck is in there? Huh?

780
01:05:43.444 --> 01:05:46.113
[Rachel gasping]

781
01:05:54.321 --> 01:05:57.124
[footsteps on stairs]

782
01:06:00.862 --> 01:06:02.129
[Garrick]
Get up.

783
01:06:03.030 --> 01:06:04.231
Slowly.

784
01:06:08.736 --> 01:06:10.037
Turn around.

785
01:06:10.705 --> 01:06:12.039
Turn around!

786
01:06:12.039 --> 01:06:13.942
[Rachel] I don't know
what happened.

787
01:06:14.041 --> 01:06:16.477
She... I...

788
01:06:16.544 --> 01:06:19.246
I don't...
I don't know what happened.

789
01:06:19.313 --> 01:06:22.650
-Put her down!
-I don't think she's breathing!

790
01:06:22.717 --> 01:06:24.719
Put my baby down!

791
01:06:25.753 --> 01:06:29.089
[Rachel breathing shakily]

792
01:06:29.156 --> 01:06:31.391
[Garrick]
Why would you?

793
01:06:33.962 --> 01:06:35.797
-[gasps]
-Look at him!

794
01:06:35.864 --> 01:06:38.065
How? How could you?!

795
01:06:38.098 --> 01:06:41.736
No. please! I don't
know what's happening!

796
01:06:46.574 --> 01:06:47.575
[crying] No!

797
01:06:47.642 --> 01:06:48.576
No!

798
01:06:48.643 --> 01:06:51.311
No! No!

799
01:06:51.378 --> 01:06:52.580
No!

800
01:06:52.647 --> 01:06:57.084
[sobbing]

801
01:07:04.526 --> 01:07:07.662
[vomiting]

802
01:07:07.729 --> 01:07:09.463
[growling]

803
01:07:09.531 --> 01:07:11.431
[shouts]

804
01:07:13.768 --> 01:07:14.903
-No!
-[gunshot]

805
01:07:14.969 --> 01:07:16.538
[Rachel gasps]

806
01:07:20.775 --> 01:07:23.110
[gurgling]

807
01:07:31.986 --> 01:07:34.388
[sobbing]

808
01:07:41.729 --> 01:07:44.666
[baby crying in distance]

809
01:07:55.843 --> 01:07:58.445
[squeaking]

810
01:08:32.412 --> 01:08:33.815
[wind whooshes]

811
01:08:37.085 --> 01:08:38.620
[gasps]

812
01:08:45.593 --> 01:08:46.661
[gasping]

813
01:08:46.728 --> 01:08:49.063
[snarling]

814
01:08:49.196 --> 01:08:50.230
No.

815
01:08:50.297 --> 01:08:52.600
[snarling]

816
01:08:59.107 --> 01:09:02.275
[gasps]

817
01:09:13.821 --> 01:09:16.223
[breathing heavily]

818
01:09:19.927 --> 01:09:22.797
-[kalimba music]
-[crying]

819
01:09:24.932 --> 01:09:26.901
[monitor crackling]

820
01:09:26.968 --> 01:09:28.102
Laura.

821
01:09:28.235 --> 01:09:31.639
[indistinct whispers]

822
01:09:32.807 --> 01:09:34.241
What?

823
01:09:54.128 --> 01:09:57.532
[baby crying]

824
01:09:57.598 --> 01:10:00.702
[distorted]
Give me my baby back!

